# Sales & Profitability Analysis for a Retail Superstore

## Business Context
A retail superstore wants to understand its sales performance, profitability drivers, and loss-making areas across regions, categories, and shipping modes.

## Business Questions
- Which regions and categories drive maximum sales and profit?
- Which products and sub-categories are consistently loss-making?
- How do discounts and shipping modes impact profitability?
- What trends are visible over time?

## Dataset
- Superstore Sales Dataset
- Records: Orders, Customers, Products, Sales, Profit, Discounts
- Time Period: Multiple years

## Approach
The analysis was conducted in three layers:
1. Executive overview of sales and profit
2. Deep dive into profitability and risk areas
3. Trend and behavioral analysis

## Dashboards Created
1. Executive Sales Overview Dashboard  
2. Profitability & Risk Analysis Dashboard  

## Key Insights
- Central region shows high sales but lower profit margins due to heavy discounting
- Tables and Bookcases generate consistent losses across regions
- Standard Class shipping has the highest order volume but lower profitability
- High discounts strongly correlate with negative profit for select sub-categories

## Business Recommendations
- Revisit discount strategy for loss-making sub-categories
- Optimize product mix in Central and South regions
- Review shipping cost structures for Standard Class orders
- Focus promotions on high-margin product categories

## Tools Used
- Tableau Desktop
- Excel
